  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Determine if attaining aerobic fitness is beneficial in producing cortical neuroplasticity in
      individuals with chronic stroke.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Crossover clinical trial. Experimental group undergoes 3x/wk/6 months of aerobic
      conditioning. Control group performs usual daily activities. All participants will be
      assessed with cognitive and motor behavioral testing at baseline, 3, 6, 9 and 12 months.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
